passages.text: “Rap” represents Rapamycin treatment; “Eve” represents Everolimus treatment. “↓” indicates siRNA knockdown of the gene sensitizes to the Rapamycin and/or Everolimus response (P < 0.05). “↑” indicates siRNA knockdown of gene desensitizes to the Rapamycin and/or Everolimus response (P < 0.05). “Yes” indicates miR-10a was verified to regulate gene expression. Blank indicates no significant change in cytotoxicity after knockdown.
